# Hand-written parser-error-message overrides for the Wax grammar
# (ERROR-MESSAGES.md step 5). Keyed by the *sentence* an error state's
# --list-errors representative carries ("entry_point: sentence"); merged by
# scripts/generate_error_messages.ml after generation. See the WAT companion
# file (src/lib-wasm/parser_messages.overrides) for the full format and the
# rot-protection contract.
#
# These are the 34 structurally immovable over-5 fallbacks. Thirty-two are
# expression-FOLLOW states: after a complete expression the parser accepts an
# infix operator, one of the postfix operators, or a closer that ends the
# expression — a set that always overflows the readable cap, so the generated
# message degrades to a bare "Syntax error". One uniform, honest message serves
# them all. The remaining two are a labeled-block head and a function type in a
# type position (a type definition or an '&fn(…)' reference type; the function
# and tag *declaration* signature was split off to its own rule and no longer
# needs an override).

# --- Expression-FOLLOW states (uniform message) ---
# After a complete expression: extend it with an operator / postfix, or end it.

parse: CONST IDENT EQUAL CHAR BANGEQUAL CHAR EQUAL
Expecting an operator, a postfix operator ('.', '[', '(', '!', 'as', 'is', 'on', or '?'), or the end of the expression.

parse: CONST IDENT EQUAL CHAR EQUALEQUAL CHAR EQUAL
Expecting an operator, a postfix operator ('.', '[', '(', '!', 'as', 'is', 'on', or '?'), or the end of the expression.

