# state 329: expression-FOLLOW inside descriptor( … ); the same message, plus a
# hint at the still-open '(' of the descriptor operand.
parse: FN IDENT LBRACE LBRACE DESCRIPTOR LPAREN CHAR ELSE
Expecting an operator, a postfix operator ('.', '[', '(', '!', 'as', 'is', 'on', or '?'), or the end of the expression.
<2>This '(' opens the enclosing construct.

# --- Non-expression states ---

# state 226: after a block label 'l:, a labeled block must follow.
parse: FN IDENT LBRACE QUOTE AS COLON UNREACHABLE
Expecting a labeled block: 'do', 'while', 'loop', 'if', 'try', or 'try_legacy'.

# state 56: after a function-type parameter list in a *type* position — a type
# definition ('type f = fn(…)') or a reference type inside an expression
# ('x as &fn(…)'). A result type ('->') or, in the expression home, an operator /
# a postfix / the enclosing block's '{' / the end of the expression may follow.
# The function/tag *declaration* signature no longer merges here: it is the
# phantom-parameter instantiation 'function_type(in_declaration)' (this state is
# 'function_type(in_type)'), whose own state auto-generates
# "Expecting ''', '->', ';', or '{'.", so this state and its message are now the
# type home alone.
parse: TYPE IDENT EQUAL FN LPAREN RPAREN WHILE
Expecting '->', '{', an operator, a postfix operator ('.', '[', '(', '!', 'as', 'is', 'on', or '?'), or the end of the expression.

